analysis: The documents primarily concern the establishment and modification of agencies and programs during the Great Depression and the early New Deal era. They focus on economic recovery, relief efforts, and adjustments to government operations in response to the crisis. Several documents reference and utilize the authority granted by acts such as the National Industrial Recovery Act and the Emergency Relief Appropriation Act. They also deal with specific issues like rural mail delivery, cost of living adjustments for government employees, and the creation of entities like the Commodity Credit Corporation and the Resettlement Administration.
title: New Deal Agency & Program Implementation
